Still, independently of the Categories, the balance of evidence isin favour of ranking Aristotle amongst the oppo- nents of the doctrines which were subsequently designated as Realist. It must be remembered, however, that the precise question agitated by the Schoolmen had not been raised in his time. On the subject of Aristotle’s opinions in relation to this controversy, it is impossible to enter hereat any length, but the student may read with advantage Haureau’s Histoire de la Philosophie Scolastique, ch. 5, and Ueberweg’s History of Philosophy, On Aristotle's Metaphysics (Translatiom vol. i. pp. 160-1).
